HEADWORD: orthodontia
<hw>orthodontia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The treatment
of the teeth so as to make the teeth align properly within the mouth,
usually involving the wearing of braces and sometimes oral
surgery.</def>⟦br⟧
